<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3670878>
    dc:description "FIGURES 411–422. Wings: 411: Fergusonina sp. (Fergusoninidae); 412: Odontoloxozus longicornis (Coquillett) (Neriidae); 413: Clisa australis (McAlpine) (Cypselosomatidae); 414: Formicosepsis sp. (Cypselosomatidae); 415: Pseudopomyza (Rhinopomyzella) nigrimana Hennig (Pseudopomyzidae); 416: Latheticomyia sp. (Pseudopomyzidae); 417: Nartshukia musiva Shatalkin, holotype (Strongylophthalmyiidae); 418: Strongylophthalmyia angustipennis Melander (Strongylophthalmyiidae); 419: Tanypeza longimana Fallén (Tanypezidae); 420: Neotanypeza marshalli Lonsdale (Tanypezidae); 421: Compsobata mima (Hennig) (Micropezidae); 422: Micropeza sp. (Micropezidae)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3670878/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3670831>
    dc:description "FIGURES 233–243. Figs 233–237: Heloclusia imperfecta Malloch (Pseudopomyzidae); 233: female dorsal; 234: same, lateral; 235: head anterior; 236: head dorsal; 237: male, Chile. Figs 238–241: Latheticomyia sp. (Pseudopomyzidae), male; 238: head, anterior; 239: head, dorsal; 240: dorsal; 241: lateral. Fig. 242: Pseudopomyza atrimana (Meigen) (Pseudopomyzidae), head anterior. Fig. 243: Pseudopomyza (Rhinopomyzella) sp., dorsal." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3670831/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3670833>
    dc:description "FIGURES 244–249. Pseudopomyza atrimana (Meigen) (Pseudopomyzidae), male terminalia; 244: lateral; 245: external genitalia, posterior; 246: same, anterior; 247: sternites 6–8, ventral; 248: internal genitalia, ventral; 249: same, left lateral." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3670833/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3670835>
    dc:description "FIGURES 250–256. Figs 250–251: Latheticomyia sp. (Pseudopomyzidae), female abdomen; 250: ventral; 251: lateral. Figs 252–256: Pseudopomyza atrimana (Meigen) (Pseudopomyzidae), female abdomen; 252: segments 4 to cerci (terminalia retracted), ventral; 253: segment 7, lateral; 254: segment 10 and cerci, ventral; 255: same, dorsal; 256: internal genitalia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3670835/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

